{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c7b4ca88-d6c9-4d8a-8efa-107274b60dba","content":"Here's the evaluation performance analysis for this project:\n\n## Issues Found\n\n### 1. File I/O Property Function (High Impact)\n**Line 13 in `EvalHeavy.csproj`:**\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\nProperty functions that perform file I/O execute during **every evaluation** (design-time builds, IDE reload, etc.). This blocks the evaluation thread on disk access.\n\n**Fix:** Move file reading to a target with `Inputs/Outputs` so it only runs at build time, or use a build task instead.\n\n### 2. Expensive Recursive Glob (Medium Impact)\n**Line 9:**\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\n`**\\*.*` walks the entire directory tree during evaluation. As the repo grows, this becomes progressively slower. It also captures unintended files (images, binaries, etc.).\n\n**Fix:** Narrow the glob to specific extensions (e.g., `**\\*.txt`) or add more exclusions via `DefaultItemExcludes`.\n\n### 3. Deep Import Chain (Low-Medium Impact)\n```\nEvalHeavy.csproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props\n```\nA 3-level chain here is modest, but this pattern scales poorly. Each import adds an evaluation pass. In larger repos this can exceed 20+ levels and noticeably slow evaluation.\n\n**Fix:** Flatten imports where possible or consolidate settings.\n\n---\n\n**Priority order:** Fix the `File::ReadAllText` call first (most impactful), then narrow the glob, then consider flattening imports.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fb1320ee-7c9d-4b6e-a425-41af09367ebb","outputTokens":419,"requestId":"2843:20DE42:2CDA50:341488:69FA958F"},"id":"f4807249-6f19-4fe7-a001-a9cfaf66b26d","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:12:59.024Z","parentId":"6e7784ed-a460-457b-8af4-2b161bca6ef5"}
